  "text": "## General Questions  \n**Q: Is my money protected if FirstUK Bank fails?**\nA: Yes. Financial Services Compensation Scheme (FSCS) protects up to £85,000 per customer.  \n**Q: What is the debit card limit for contactless payments?**\nA: £100 per transaction. No PIN required below this limit.  \n**Q: Can I get interest statements?**\nA: Yes. Email support@firstuk.bank to request statement of interest earned.  \n**Q: How do I update my contact details?**\nA:\n- Online: Update in account settings\n- Phone: Call 0800-555-2265\n- Branch: Visit in person  \n**Q: Can I change the account holder details after opening?**\nA: No. Account holder cannot be changed. You can close and open a new account in different name.  \n---",
